Just installed Code 0.10.10 on Windows 8.1 and installed PowerShell x86 debugger extension.
If I click the green triangle, it runs my program. If I hover over the green triangle, I get a hover message "Start (F5)", but if I press F5, I get a file explorer opened to the workspace root. I looked in Microsoft Mouse and Keyboard Center and found that the F5 key was set to the Open function. I changed the setting to Disable this key and now F5 does nothing in Code (even after restarting Code). Here is my launch.json file:

```
{
    "version": "0.2.0",
    "configurations": [
        {
            "name": "PowerShell x86",
            "type": "PowerShell x86",
            "request": "launch",
            "program": "${workspaceRoot}\\Compare.ps1",
            "args": ["arg1", "arg2", "arg3"]
            //"cwd": ""
        }
    ]
}
```

SCM telemetry events used to be prefixed with `workbench.action.git.*`, this made it possible to track all SCM activity based on the event name prefix. Now I noticed it's not the case anymore, causing all of our reports related to SCM usage to drop. I will be reprocessing those but I think we need to get back to prefix those events for easier processing in the future. 

I suggest something as `workbench.action.scm.*`. 

